author: Matthew Brooker
text: So this is just pyrolysis. An old technology which, upon superficial inspection, looks like it could solve any plastic pollution issues. However, the reason that this has not taken off in the developed world is because of the potent mix of emissions created as a by product of the fuel conversion process. Incineration is cleaner, but I guess you have to trade off the science with the social benefits in this case. But a panacea this solution is not.

reply.author: dragonshivu
reply.text:
I understand you are frustrated that they have not added any sources or link to the websites of the people behind the project. 

Let me get to your points:
1. The process mentioned in the video is thermal catalytic depolymerization (TCD) which has been a well known process for a while now. TCD is used in converting biomass into biofuel. But here they are using the similar process into breaking down plastic. This process is energy inefficient and costly for recyclers to run, but has come a long way in terms of adoption.

2. I‚Äôll not go into why you don‚Äôt believe in that website. I don‚Äôt the responses are doctored but they are made into a story which has a good flow that you can understand. You need to know that they are trying to condense a story of the person who goes from using wood to clean fuel. That doesn‚Äôt happen overnight.

3. Links to everything I mentioned: 
https://rudraenvsolution.com/


https://www.e3s-conferences.org/articles/e3sconf/pdf/2017/02/e3sconf_ef2017_02044.pdf

author: Shrey Bhardwaj
text:
My sister vishakha bhardwaj and I have devised a solar powered fully automatic system that can clean solid floating waste from flowing water bodies(mainly rivers).we lost our patience with marine pollution a long ago.picking marine solid 
floating waste manually is inefficient and using boat to do so is costly. 
According to an estimate $13billion a year is losses from damage to marine 
ecosystem, including financial losses to fisheries and tourism. 
Plastic breaks down to micro plastic it then get into food chain increasing 
the risk of human infertility, birthdefects &cancer. 8 out of 10 babies and 
nearly all adults have measurable amount of plastic in their bodies.micro 
plastic are the result of floating plastic waste which is constantly exposed 
to UV radiation and crumbles into smaller smaller pieces.
We need help to make this project implemented in rivers  with the support of Indian    government and some investors investors .

reply.author: Aaron Jackson
reply.text:
@Yogesh Desai; I am not sure where you reside Sir, however, in America and Western Europe we also, did NOT hear of these types of innovations through our Media.  The problem with our Media is not necessarily the Policy, as we have a concept known as 'Freedom of Press'-Also Known As-FREE SPEECH, however, the Media here is rarely 'Independent Media' which means that the Governments or the Corporations or the Oligarchs or a combination of these Entities OWN our Media. Hence, we hear the same 'Broken Record' that plays in Developing Countries or Countries with Oppressive Governments or War Torn Countries.  See, the difference between America/Western European/Developed Countries and those Countries with Oppressive Governments/War Torn Countries/Developing Countries is only ONE ISSUE, and this is in the Western-'Developed World'-our Governments Blatantly LIE to us through the spread of PROPAGANDA and MISINFORMATION, (to keep our citizens quarrelling amongst ourselves, so as to pay no mind to the bona fide problems mounting all around us), where as, in the 'Developing Countries' of the World, those Governments feel that they have NO NEED TO LIE, because, they have such a strangle hold on the Peoples and Societies they are ruling over. 
Either way, this is no way to treat people and the INEQUALITY, no matter what part of the World one resides in, MUST COME TO AN END!!! 
How to achieve this, is a concept I believe I am not capable of understanding, for I fear a great deal of us who are already suffering, in a kind of Purgatory, for the benefits of those in a Caste far higher than mine own, will continue to suffer, and probably much, much worse!
Your Friend and Ally,
Aaron Andrew.
